markets.title: Will the spot price of Solana be above $294.096 before Jan 1, 2026 at 10:00 AM ET ET?
markets.rules_primary: If the spot price of Solana is above 294.096 before 10:00 AM ET on Jan 1, 2026, then the market resolves to Yes.
markets.rules_secondary: The spot price of Solana is measured in U.S. dollars according to the CF Solana-Dollar Real Time Index (SOLUSD_RTI). The price is monitored continuously between market issuance and the specified date and time. For resolution, a simple average of the SOLUSD_RTI values for each minute after issuance and prior to the specified time on the date is calculated. For the "above" operator, the price must strictly exceed the threshold value at any point. For the "below" operator, the price must remain strictly less than the threshold throughout the entire period. The market resolves to Yes as soon as the price criterion is met for "above" markets, while "below" markets only resolve after the deadline if price never exceeded the threshold.
markets.early_close_condition: This market will close and expire early if Solana reaches the specified price threshold.
